The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new sampling scheme for object detection, which is a sub-topic of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of fine-grained image classification, which is a sub-topic of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
